^FB(162.93,15,2,14,0)="38 CFR 17.1002  Substantive conditions for payment or reimbursement."
^FB(162.93,15,2,15,0)="--------------------------------------------------------------------"
^FB(162.93,15,2,16,0)="    Payment or reimbursement under 38 U.S.C. 1725 for emergency "
^FB(162.93,15,2,17,0)="services may be made only if all of the following conditions are met:"
^FB(162.93,15,2,18,0)="    (a) The emergency services were provided in a hospital emergency "
^FB(162.93,15,2,19,0)="department or a similar facility held out as providing emergency care "
^FB(162.93,15,2,20,0)="to the public;"
^FB(162.93,15,2,21,0)="    (b) The claim for payment or reimbursement for the initial "
^FB(162.93,15,2,22,0)="evaluation and treatment is for a condition of such a nature that a "
^FB(162.93,15,2,23,0)="prudent layperson would have reasonably expected that delay in seeking "
^FB(162.93,15,2,24,0)="immediate medical attention would have been hazardous to life or health "
^FB(162.93,15,2,25,0)="(this standard would be met if there were an emergency medical "
^FB(162.93,15,2,26,0)="condition manifesting itself by acute symptoms of sufficient severity "
^FB(162.93,15,2,27,0)="(including severe pain) that a prudent layperson who possesses an "
^FB(162.93,15,2,28,0)="average knowledge of health and medicine could reasonably expect the "
^FB(162.93,15,2,29,0)="absence of immediate medical attention to result in placing the health "
^FB(162.93,15,2,30,0)="of the individual in serious jeopardy, serious impairment to bodily "
^FB(162.93,15,2,31,0)="functions, or serious dysfunction of any bodily organ or part);"
^FB(162.93,15,2,32,0)="    (c) A VA or other Federal facility/provider was not feasibly "
^FB(162.93,15,2,33,0)="available and an attempt to use them beforehand would not have been "
^FB(162.93,15,2,34,0)="considered reasonable by a prudent layperson (as an example, these "
^FB(162.93,15,2,35,0)="conditions would be met by evidence establishing that a veteran was "
^FB(162.93,15,2,36,0)="brought to a hospital in an ambulance and the ambulance personnel "
^FB(162.93,15,2,37,0)="determined that the nearest available appropriate level of care was at "
^FB(162.93,15,2,38,0)="a non-VA medical center);"
^FB(162.93,15,2,39,0)="    (d) The claim for payment or reimbursement for any medical care "
^FB(162.93,15,2,40,0)="beyond the initial emergency evaluation and treatment is for a "
^FB(162.93,15,2,41,0)="continued medical emergency of such a nature that the veteran could not "
^FB(162.93,15,2,42,0)="have been safely transferred to a VA or other Federal facility (the "
^FB(162.93,15,2,43,0)="medical emergency lasts only until the time the veteran becomes "
^FB(162.93,15,2,44,0)="stabilized);"
^FB(162.93,15,2,45,0)="    (e) At the time the emergency treatment was furnished, the veteran "
^FB(162.93,15,2,46,0)="was enrolled in the VA health care system and had received medical "
^FB(162.93,15,2,47,0)="services under authority of 38 U.S.C. chapter 17 within the 24-month "
^FB(162.93,15,2,48,0)="period preceding the furnishing of such emergency treatment;"
^FB(162.93,15,2,49,0)="    (f) The veteran is financially liable to the provider of emergency "
^FB(162.93,15,2,50,0)="treatment for that treatment;"
^FB(162.93,15,2,51,0)="    (g) The veteran has no coverage under a health-plan contract for "
^FB(162.93,15,2,52,0)="payment or reimbursement, in whole or in part, for the emergency "
^FB(162.93,15,2,53,0)="treatment (this condition cannot be met if the veteran has coverage "
^FB(162.93,15,2,54,0)="under a health-plan contract but payment is barred because of a failure "
^FB(162.93,15,2,55,0)="by the veteran or the provider to comply with the provisions of that "
^FB(162.93,15,2,56,0)="health-plan contract, e.g., failure to submit a bill or medical records "
^FB(162.93,15,2,57,0)="within specified time limits, or failure to exhaust appeals of the "
^FB(162.93,15,2,58,0)="denial of payment);"
^FB(162.93,15,2,59,0)="    (h) If the condition for which the emergency treatment was "
^FB(162.93,15,2,60,0)="furnished was caused by an accident or work-related injury, the "
^FB(162.93,15,2,61,0)="claimant has exhausted without success all claims and remedies "
^FB(162.93,15,2,62,0)="reasonably available to the veteran or provider against a third party "
^FB(162.93,15,2,63,0)="for payment of such treatment; and the veteran has no contractual or "
^FB(162.93,15,2,64,0)="legal recourse against a third party that could reasonably be pursued "
^FB(162.93,15,2,65,0)="for the purpose of extinguishing, in whole or in part, the veteran's "
^FB(162.93,15,2,66,0)="liability to the provider; and"
^FB(162.93,15,2,67,0)="    (i) The veteran is not eligible for reimbursement under 38 U.S.C. "
^FB(162.93,15,2,68,0)="1728 for the emergency treatment provided (38 U.S.C. 1728 authorizes VA "
^FB(162.93,15,2,69,0)="payment or reimbursement for emergency treatment to a limited group of "
^FB(162.93,15,2,70,0)="veterans, primarily those who receive emergency treatment for a "
^FB(162.93,15,2,71,0)="service-connected disability)."
^FB(162.93,15,2,72,0)=" "
^FB(162.93,15,2,73,0)="(Authority: 38 U.S.C. 1725)"
